                <h2>Jobs</h2>
                                <h3>Level  1 Certificate in MOSING</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Entry requirements: Successful interview</h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Duration: One Year - Part time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <p>This course is based on the knowledge and practical skills needed for a sphax pure bd craft sprite Artist. The course is a Part time course that is split into two, sprite work, and Testing work. The course has 5 main elements.
                                </p>
                                <h3>Level 1 Certificate in Obeying Orders</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Entry requirements: Successful interview</h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Duration: One Year - Part time time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <p>This Certificate is good for entry sprite Artists for whom traditional examinations may not be appropriate. This course is a base level qualification which usually leads to level  1 and level 2 in MOS orders and Testing. 
                                </p>
                                <h3>Level 1 Diploma in MOS Orders</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1>Experience needed: 4 MUSHs at grade C or above. Level 1 Technical work or equivalent experience and knowledge.
                                </h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1>Duration: One Year - Part time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <p>This course will set you up for a career in the MOS sprite division.  This course includes 
Maintaining positive working relationships.
Routine Technical maintenance.

Doing the following: MOS Phone Sprite, Make a game and Script it, Make some sphax Art and components.
</p>
                                <h3>Level 2 Diploma in Art (Order is level 1)</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Entry requirements: 4 MUSHs at grade B or above. </h1>
                                <br>
                                
                                <br>
                                <p>
                                This course is designed to provide you with a specialist work-related qualification and training in marine engineering. The course provides sound preparation for those seeking an apprenticeship or progression to a higher level course such as the National Diploma. This course includes several different parts:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Introduction to the Marine Industry
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Health and safety requirements
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Marina and boatyard facilities
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Types of boats and their features
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Marine terminology
                                </p>
                                <h3>Level 3 diploma in engineering (electrical and electronic)</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1>Entry requirements: 5 GCSEs at grade C or above including Maths, English and Science, or a Level 2 qualification in Engineering.</h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Duration: Two Years – Full time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <p>This course will provide you with an understanding of the complex design, manufacture, and maintenance and flight characteristics of both rotary wing and fixed wing aircraft. Our aerospace engineering workshop is well-equipped and features a full-size helicopter.
                                </p>
                                <h3>Level 3 diploma in engineering (marine-NCFE)</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1>Entry Requirements: intermediate Diploma in Marine Engineering</h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Duration: Two Years – Full time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <p>
                                This is the follow on from the level 2 qualification.  It consolidates the skills taught and further progresses to securing an apprenticeship or further study.  This topic allows you to look at four particular areas. Fault finding, maintenance, Diagnostics and Engine repair.

Assessment is largely by coursework.
                                </p>
                                <h3>Level 3 Diploma in Engineering (Mechanical)</h3>
                                <br>
                                <h1>Entry Requirements: 5 GCSEs at grade C or above including Maths, English and Science, or a Level 2 qualification in Engineering. Duration-two years- full time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Duration: Two Years – Full time</h1>
                                <p>On this course, you will develop a creative approach to analysis and problem solving with regard to the design, manufacture and maintenance of mechanical systems. With well equipped workshops with lather and milling machine, CAD Software and 3D printer.  
                                </p>
                                <h3>Level 3 Diploma in Motor Accident Repair </h13
                                <br>
                                <h1>Entry Requirments: 5 GCSEs at grade C or above including Maths and English (desirable) and/or Level 2 Automotive qualification. </h1>
                                <br>
                                <h1> Duration: One Year – Full time</h1>
                                <br>
                                <p>
                                This qualification is the final step towards becoming a qualified mechanic with the Level 3 technical certification. The course covers a range of skills and knowledge including:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Health, safety and good housekeeping
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                supporting job roles
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Materials, fabrication, tools and measuring devices
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Removing and fitting electronically controlled mechanical components
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Removing and fitting vehicle electronic components and systems
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Removing, refurbishing and fitting trim components
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                Level 3 Diploma in Motor Sport 5 GCSEs at grade C or above including maths and English and/or a Level 1/2 Motor Vehicle qualification.
